	<div>Eric Yaverbaum and Marc DiMassimo (two savvy marketers) have launched a campaign to turn&nbsp;September&nbsp;18 a national day of offlining - a digital sabbath:</div>
<p />
<blockquote style="margin: 0 0 0 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;">
<div>"Try making an Offlining Resolution. Have an Offline Father&rsquo;s Day. Consider committing to a weekly Offline Sabbath. We think you&rsquo;ll be glad you did, and we&rsquo;re pretty sure you&rsquo;ll find others who are glad too."</div>
</blockquote>
<p>They put together some clever viral graphics as well. September 18, notably, is Yom Kippur. <a href="http://www.offlininginc.com/?page_id=68">There's a pledge too</a>. Count me out.</p>
